Body almost entirely covered by plates except for region overlying opening of swim bladder capsule, area between pectoral girdle and lower lip, region around anus, and area around base of paired fins. Rostral plate with posterior notch articulation with mesethmoid. Rostral plate thickened, with narrow odontode-free band between dorsad and ventrad series of odontodes (
Fig. 29
), sometimes absent at medial portion of some specimens. Snout plates anterior to nares reduced, small unplated area between rostrum and nostril at lateral portion.

Two or three rows of predorsal plates (rarely two). Lateral line incomplete, with small gap without pores along middle length of body. Median plate series truncated (
Fig. 4d
). Abdominal plates arranged in three rows anteriorly and irregularly arranged between pelvic-fin insertions. Lateral abdominal plates slightly larger and forming regular series. Median abdominal series.
